The paper deals with a problem in graph theory related to routing and flow, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Graph Theory (cs.GT), or Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The fact that the problem is shown to be NP-complete and has been studied in the context of parameterized complexity also supports these categories. However, since the paper specifically focuses on the planar case, cs.CG and cs.GT seem more likely than the others.
